 263:     def get_molecule_change_matrix(self, positions, rotation, translation, cell, centering):


 264:         #


 265:         #    Note: Calculates new type of molecule change matrix that contains information about in which cell the atom switched in place was of the atom


 266:         #


 267:         cdef np.ndarray[np.int8_t, ndim=1] result = np.zeros(positions.shape[0], dtype=np.int8)


 268:         result.fill(-1)


 269:         cdef np.ndarray[np.int8_t, ndim=2] original_cell_displacement = np.zeros((positions.shape[0], 3), dtype=np.int8)


 270:         displacement_vectors = []


 271:         for x in range(-3, 3):


 272:             for y in range(-3, 3):


 273:                 for z in range(-3, 3):


 274:                     displacement_vectors.append(np.array([x, y, z]))


 275:         for displacement_vector in displacement_vectors:


 276:             if -1 in result:


 277:                 displacement = np.dot(displacement_vector, cell)


 278:                 new_positions = apply_symmetry_operation_to_coordinates(positions + displacement, rotation, np.dot(translation, cell), centering = centering)


 279:                 for i, position in enumerate(positions):


 280:                     if result[i] == -1:


 281:                         result[i] = equal_position_found(new_positions, position, max_error=0.01)


 282:                         original_cell_displacement[i] = np.array(displacement_vector, dtype=np.int8)


 283:         if -1 in result:


 284:             print "ERRORORRR! Replacing atom not found"


 285:             raw_input()


 286: 


 287: 


 288:         #cdef np.ndarray[np.int8_t, ndim = 2] returned = np.array([result, original_cell_displacement], dtype=np.int8)


 289:         return result, original_cell_displacement
